##18:10 Tuesday 24 February 2015 JST##
At the toy store, I found some sets of themed images drawn on some cards, copyright Stephanie Graegin and produced by eeBoo corporation. I thought &ldquo;these would be useful during my lessons,&rdquo; thinking my students might enjoy making stories with the cards as prompts. Then I was like, &ldquo;AND I can use them in my Japanese lessons!!&rdquo;
I got the &ldquo;Animal Village&rdquo; set, so I&rsquo;m about to learn nouns in Japanese like fox, skunk, porcupine, squirrel, and platypus&hellip; plus campfire, guitar, marshmallow (though I bet the last two are just カタ カナ versions of English words).
